descript.purpose: On November 2, 1993, the Voters of San Diego County approved the Forest Conservation Initiative (FCI). Along with changes to the Countyâ€™s General Plan, the Initiative also required the County to place a minimum parcel size of 40 acres with a maximum density one dwelling unit per parcel on all parcels affected by the Initiative. The Initiative affected approximately 83,000 acres in the County. Those acres are located in the Pendleton-DeLuz, North Mountain, Ramona, Julian, Central Mountain, Mountain Empire, Desert and Jamul/Dulzura Community and Subregional Plan Areas.
